release.body:
##  Breaking Change  Manual Migration Required

The integration domain has been renamed from  
`gruenbeck_softliQ_SC`  `gruenbeck_softliq_sc`  
to comply with Home Assistant naming conventions and to align with the icon integration.

To preserve your existing configuration:
Due to the renaming HACS will install this integration under a new lower cased folder (linux subsystem are case sensitive). 
This will make both integration installed the 0.3.x and 0.4.0 will be available. Still the domain of the new integration has changed and the existing entities need to me moved to the new domain. 

 **After updating in HACS, go to Settings  Devices & Services  Add Integration  search for Grnbeck SoftliQ SC (with the icon) and start the configuration flow.**

The Configuration flow of the 0.4 Version will automatically migrate your existing setup:
- All devices  
- All entities (including names, areas, and history/statistics)

 After HACS installed the new Version 0.4.0 the old version is still installed in the camel cased folder and will show the entities as active. Even if the Icon is shown please cross check the Version of the integration. If still < 0.4.0 try to re add the integration in the correct version. 

---

## Post-Installation Cleanup

- After the integration has been added successfully and the entities are migrated, the **old `gruenbeck_softliQ_SC` folder** under `custom_components` can be removed manually.  
- This cleanup step is optional but recommended to avoid confusion.

---

## Changes

- **Renamed integration domain**: `gruenbeck_softliQ_SC`  `gruenbeck_softliq_sc`
- Added automatic migration for existing configurations
- Updated integration icon for easier discovery in the Add Integration flow
- **Dependency updates**:
  - `homeassistant==2025.8.2`  
  - `ruff==0.5.3`  
  - `aiohttp==3.12.15`  

---
